<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="17" type="distribution">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="17">Distribution and habitat.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="17">
<taxonomicName authorityName="G. Q. Hao, J. Quan Liu &amp; Al-Shehbaz" authorityYear="2018" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Brassicaceae" genus="Eutrema" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Eutrema nanum" order="Brassicales" pageId="0" pageNumber="17" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="nanum">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="17">Eutrema nanum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is currently known only from Chola Shan, part of Hengduan Mountains in West Sichuan, China (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 3" captionStartId="F3" captionText="Figure 3. Geographical distribution of the sampled populations of Eutrema nanum and related species." figureDoi="10.3897/phytokeys.109.27049.figure3" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/228467" pageId="0" pageNumber="17">3</figureCitation>
). It grows under rocks by streams close to glaciers, damp or gravelly scree, wet sand at a very high elevation of 4500-4600 m.
</paragraph>
